  "local_port": 56696,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What topics should I follow on Quora? Why?",
  "response": "Choosing topics to follow on Quora depends on your interests, goals, and what you hope to gain from the platform. Here\u2019s a guide to help you decide, along with reasons for each:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Topics That Align With Your Interests**\n   - **Examples:** Technology, literature, travel, fitness, gaming, art, etc.\n   - **Why:** Following topics you\u2019re passionate about ensures you see content that excites and engages you. It\u2019s a great way to stay updated, learn new things, and connect with like-minded people.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Professional Development**\n   - **Examples:** Career advice, entrepreneurship, leadership, personal finance, marketing, etc.\n   - **Why:** These topics can help you grow in your career, learn industry trends, and gain insights from experts. Quora is a valuable resource for knowledge-sharing in professional fields.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Personal Growth**\n   - **Examples:** Self-improvement, mindfulness, productivity, mental health, relationships, etc.\n   - **Why:** Following these topics can inspire you to become a better version of yourself, offering practical advice and perspectives on improving your life.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Current Events and News**\n   - **Examples:** Politics, global affairs, climate change, technology trends, etc.\n   - **Why:** Staying informed about the world helps you engage in meaningful conversations and make better decisions. Quora often provides diverse viewpoints on current issues.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Hobbies and Creative Pursuits**\n   - **Examples:** Photography, cooking, writing, gardening, DIY projects, etc.\n   - **Why:** These topics can spark creativity, provide inspiration, and help you improve your skills in areas you enjoy.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Science and Education**\n   - **Examples:** Physics, biology, history, philosophy, psychology, etc.\n   - **Why:** Following these topics can satisfy your curiosity, deepen your understanding of the world, and expose you to fascinating ideas.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Pop Culture and Entertainment**\n   - **Examples:** Movies, music, TV shows, celebrity news, etc.\n   - **Why:** If you enjoy staying up-to-date with entertainment or engaging in discussions about pop culture, these topics are a fun way to do so.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Quora Insights and Best Practices**\n   - **Examples:** Writing tips, Quora strategies, content creation, etc.\n   - **Why:** If you\u2019re an active Quora user or looking to grow your presence on the platform, these topics can help you understand how to write effective answers, gain followers, and engage with the community.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Niche Topics**\n   - **Examples:** Rare hobbies, specific industries, local events, etc.\n   - **Why:** Following niche topics allows you to dive deep into specialized areas and connect with people who share your unique interests.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Inspiration and Motivation**\n   - **Examples:** Success stories, motivational quotes, life lessons, etc.\n   - **Why:** These topics can uplift you, provide encouragement, and remind you of the possibilities in life.\n\n---\n\n### How to Decide:\n- **Ask Yourself:** What do I want to learn? What excites me? What can help me grow?\n- **Experiment:** Follow a mix of topics initially and adjust based on what resonates with you.\n- **Engage:** Participate in discussions to make the most of the topics you follow.\n\nBy curating your Quora feed with topics that matter to you, you\u2019ll create a valuable and personalized learning experience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
